1. git 이란
    1) VCS (Version Control System)
            ---------------
        - software
            - tracks and manages changes

    2) Git 
        - is just one VCS
        - other VCS
            - Subversion, CVS, Mercurial
        
            - Linus Torvalds
            - Coders & Engineer
            - Governments, Scientists, Writers, Anyone...

            - all on my local machine 
            - upload my history to Github to share with others

    3) Git is Primarily a Terminal Tool 
        - command-line tool 
        - various git commands
        - git GUI's 

2. Configuring Git
    - git config --global user.name "Tom Cruse"      //공백 없으면 그냥 해도 되고 공백 있으면  ""
    - git config --global user.email tom@gmail.com   //깃에 저장된 이메일 적기 

3. Repository - 저장소 
    1) Repo 
        - workspce with tracks and manages files within a folder 

4. Git Command
    1) git status
        - give information on the current status of a git repository and its contents 
    2) git init 
        - create a new fit repository
        - git tracks a directory and all nested subdirectories
        - git is now watching that!
    3) git commit

5. Committing 
    1) save
    2) snapshot 
    3) 예

    delete team. html
    modified about.html
    modified about.css
    created navbar.html
    created navbar.css
    created navbar.js 
    created logo.jpg

     Working Directory   ------------  
                                    \|/
                                    git add 
                                     |
    Staging Area    <-----------------
                                    \|/
                                    git commit
                                    \|/
     Repository     <-----------------


    
    